plan.description:
In eShopLegacyMVC, the CatalogController.AddUriPlaceHolder method is empty, which means PictureUri is never set on CatalogItem. As a result, all <img src='@item.PictureUri'/> or @Model.PictureUri references in the catalog views (CatalogTable.cshtml, Edit.cshtml, Delete.cshtml, Details.cshtml) render with no image. The eShopPorted reference implementation sets: item.PictureUri = $"/Pics/{item.Id}.png"

Implement the same logic in eShopLegacyMVC's CatalogController:
```csharp
private void AddUriPlaceHolder(CatalogItem item)
{
    item.PictureUri = $"/Pics/{item.Id}.png";
}
```

This works because the Pics/ folder (now in wwwroot/Pics/ after Step 1) contains files named 1.png, 2.png, etc., and ASP.NET Core's static file middleware serves them at /Pics/1.png etc.
